Every HTML element is either inline or Block-level Elements.
Block-Level Elements always starts from a new Line.
Inline Elements don't start on a new Line.
Block elements take up full of the avaliable width.
Inline elements takes up width as necessary as possible.
Inline Elements are nested inside the block-level Elements.

code:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Inline and Block-level Elements</h1>
    <div style="background-color: red;">A</div>
    <p><span style="background-color: blue;">B</span></p>
</body>
</html>
